# Curated kernel modules the inspector loads at startup (decision D-012).
#
# These are *base* module names; the Dockerfile resolves transitive dependencies
# and load order at build time (depmod / `modprobe --show-depends`) and ships the
# result, uncompressed, plus an ordered `beskar7.load` the binary finit_module's.
# Built-in drivers (already in the kernel) are skipped at build time.
#
# This is the Smoke 0/1 slice: virtio (QEMU/KVM) + ahci/e1000 (legacy QEMU) +
# ext4 (mandatory — the COS_OEM partition the inspector mounts is ext). The broad
# bare-metal NIC/HBA set + a PCI-modalias coldplug pass are a deliberate
# follow-up (see D-012); they are not needed for the QEMU smoke loop.

# Storage + bus (virtio for QEMU/KVM)
virtio_pci
virtio_blk
virtio_scsi

# Storage (legacy/QEMU + common bare metal)
ahci

# Networking (QEMU)
virtio_net
e1000

# Filesystem — mandatory: COS_OEM (and the deploy mount) is ext2/3/4
ext4
